nodes.title: Note ↓
widgets_values:
► CONTROLNET

• Load Image + Image Resize
  → loads image and adjusts size to match latent


♦ ControlNet — AIO (group node)

Preset sections for HED, Depth and Canny ControlNet

 — <cnet_selection>
   → select a number to activate the corresponding section
     [1=Canny | 2=Depth | 3=HED]
   → this means only one CNet will be active at a time

 — ♦ General Settings ♦
   → applies to all sections


• Preview Prep. Image
  → shows preprocessed input image to see if parameters need adjusting

=> BNB NF4 models do not work with ControlNet as of now

nodes.title: Note ↓
widgets_values:
► 2ND PASS 

• optional


♦ Sampler — Upscale w/ Model (group node)

 — <flux_guidance>
   → positive FluxGuidance scale

 — <upscale_factor>
   → defines the upscale factor (1.0 = no upscale)

 — <Use Upscale Model ?>
   — *true*  → uses chosen upscale model
   — *false* → uses regular "Upscale Image By" node

nodes.title: Note ↓
widgets_values:
► TILED DIFFUSION PASS

• can be run after 1st Pass directly
• mutually exclusive with UltimateSDUpscale Pass


♦ Sampler — Upscale w/ Model + Tiled Diffusion (group node)

 — <flux_guidance>
   → positive FluxGuidance scale

 — <upscale_factor>
   → defines the upscale factor (1.0 = no upscale)

 — <Use Upscale Model?>
   — *true*  → uses chosen upscale model
   — *false* → uses regular "Upscale Image By" node

 — <tile_size> + <tile_overlap>
   → parameters for optimal tile size calculation

 — <tile_batch_size>
   amount of tiles processed at once
   → Reduce if low on VRAM

nodes.title: Checkpoint and ControlNet Location
widgets_values:
If you already have the Flux ControlNet models and placed them into the xlabs path at : 

— models\xlabs\controlnets\

you do not need to copy the files over to your controlnet folder and waste precious space. 
Instead you can make a small change to the "extra_model_paths.yaml" file located in "ComfyUI\ComfyUI" to remedy the issue.


In case the "extra_model_paths.yaml" file was never edited before, it will have the ".example" extension, which needs to be removed for the file to take effect.
The file itself can be edited with any text editor of your choice.


Within the file the base path to your ComfyUI location has to be set.

So edit this part :

#comfyui:
# base_path: path/to/comfyui/

to :
comfyui:
base_path: DRIVE:\your_path_to_comfy\ComfyUI\ComfyUI\


and for ControlNet files located in the xlabs folder,

change this line :

# controlnet: models/controlnet/

to :
controlnet: models\xlabs\controlnets\


After restarting ComfyUI the files from the xlabs' controlnets folder will appear in dropdown menus of regular ControlNet nodes.


Another line I have changed to have the diffusion models show up in the checkpoints dropdown menus as well was
changing :

#     checkpoints: models/checkpoints/

to :
checkpoints: models\diffusion_models\

► IPADAPTER

• Load Image + ClipVision Prep Img
  → loads image and scales/crops it to a square ratio of 224x224


♦ IPAdapter — Advanced (group node)
  → simple combination of IPAdapter load and apply adv. node

 — <ipadapter>
   → select "flux-ip-adapter.safetensors" 

 — <clip_vision>
   → select "clip-vit-large-patch14.safetensors" 

 — <provider> 
   → always left it at CPU and saw no different behaviour with GPU

 — <strength_model>
   → intensity of the effect; range I usually used : 0.5-0.8

nodes.title: Note ↓
widgets_values:
► ULTIMATE UPSCALE PASS

• can be run after 1st Pass directly
• mutually exclusive with Tiled Diffusion Pass


♦ Sampler — UltimateSDUpscale (group node)

 — <flux_guidance>
   → positive FluxGuidance scale

 — <upscale_factor>
   → defines the upscale factor (1.0 = no upscale)

 — <tile_size> + <tile_overlap>
   → parameters for optimal tile size calculation

nodes.title: Note ↓
widgets_values:
► ADETAILER PASS

• can be run after any Pass
• proceeds to saving or inpainting 


♦ ADetailer — AIO (group node)


—• ♦ ♦ ♦ Detector Settings ♦ ♦ ♦

 — <bbox_detector>
   → detects bbox containing the part to be ADetailed

 — <sam_model>
   → segment-anything-model to crop the target part out of the bbox

 — <segm_detector>
   → detects the cropped out shape and masks correspondingly

 — <bbox_threshold>
   → probability of the detected part to match the query
   examples:
   — faces : detected very well → higher values work well ~0.7-0.8
   — hands : more difficult to distinguish → lower values ~0.4-0.5

 — <bbox_dilation>
   → expansion of the detected bboxes

 — <crop_factor>
   → multiple of the bbox area to be considered as context

 — <drop_size>
   → size in pixels below which a detection will be disregarded
   → to avoid over-detailing negligible background details

 
—• ♦ ♦ ♦ ADetailer Settings ♦ ♦ ♦

 — <guide_size>
   → size maximum for detections to be considered
   → allows skipping areas that are large/detailed enough already
   → when <force_inpaint> is enabled, guide_size will be disregarded

 — <inpaint_size>
   → temporary size the masked area is upscaled to during generation
     → to control level of detail
   → does nothing when the masked area is larger already

 — <feather>
   → functions as <feather> and <noise_mask_feather>

 — <noise_mask>
   —• *enabled* : 
      → context aware
      → smooth seamless result
      → <denoise> acts as denoise

   —• *disabled* : 
      → ignores context
      → allows forcing out of context content
      → requires further measures to blend in properly (inpainting)
      → <denoise> acts as opacity

 — <force_inpaint>
   → bypasses threshold and size criteria when enabled


—• ♦ ♦ ♦ Sampler Settings ♦ ♦ ♦

 — textbox at the bottom → positive conditioning

nodes.title: Solid Default Settings
widgets_values:
► DEFAULT

steps          : 20 - 50
flux_guidance  : 2  - 4
sampler        : euler
scheduler      : simple


► HYPER

steps          : 8 - 12
flux_guidance  : 1.5  - 3

nodes.title: Note ↓
widgets_values:
► 1ST PASS

 • This sampler consists of two samplers interrupted by the noise injection process. Because of that there are two separate "cfg" and "seed" settings.

 • Noise injection adds detail and allows to "reroll" the second half of the generation by changing the second seed, <NInjA seed>, altering details while keeping the base composition intact.
 → due to the first sampler's result being cached at that point already, re-generating the noise-injected part is comparatively fast


♦ Sampler — Noise Injection Alteration (NInjA) (group node)

 — <cfg> + <ninja_cfg>
   → positive FluxGuidance scale before and after noise injection

 — <ninja_seed>
   → seed of the injected noise

 — <ninja_strength>
   → amount of noise added

 — <ninja_denoise>
   → remainder of denoising steps when injecting noise
   → with 10 steps a value of 0.60 means noise is injected after step 4 with 60% of steps remaining


— avoid using the same seed for main and ninja_seed → burns the image

nodes.title: Note ↓
widgets_values:
► INPAINTING

• can be run after any Pass
• can be run repeatedly
• proceeds to saving


♦ Inpainting — AIO (group node)

—• ♦ ♦ ♦ Mask Settings ♦ ♦ ♦
 — <grow_mask>
   → expands the provided masks

 — <gaussian_blur>
   → blurs the mask for smoother integration

 
—• ♦ ♦ ♦ Inpainting Settings ♦ ♦ ♦
 — <feather>
   → functions as <feather> and <noise_mask_feather>

 — <inpaint_size>
   → temporary size the masked area is upscaled to during generation
     → to control level of detail
   → does nothing when the masked area is larger already

— <noise_mask>
   — *enabled* : 
     → context aware
     → smooth seamless result
     → <denoise> acts as denoise

   — *disabled* : 
     → ignores context
     → allows forcing out of context content
     → requires further measures to blend in properly (inpainting)
     → <denoise> acts as opacity


—• ♦ ♦ ♦ Sampler Settings ♦ ♦ ♦
 — textbox at the bottom → positive conditioning


—• ♦ ♦ ♦ Saving ♦ ♦ ♦
To save :
 → "Save Image ?" needs to be true 
 → "Save — Inpaint" in [Save Settings] has to be enabled

nodes.title: Note ↓
widgets_values:
► GENERAL SETTINGS

• "Flux Loader SWITCH"
  → Quick switch for the different Flux version loaders


♦ Loader — General (group node)
  → this behemoth of a group node takes care of most basic settings as well as meta-data processing

—• ♦ ♦ ♦ Model Sampling Flux ♦ ♦ ♦

 — <base_shift> + <max_shift>
     → higher values increase freedom during generation, resulting in more creative and detailed outcomes, but can also introduce deviations from the prompt more easily. 
     → similar to "temperature" variable for LLMs.
     → Flux Schnell models are only affected by <base_shift>


—• ♦ ♦ ♦ Latent ♦ ♦ ♦

 — <Use Resolution Preset ?>
   → determines whether resolution_preset or width+height is used


—• Accelerator LoRA

 — regular LoRA slot, secluded out of preference
   → also accounted for in the meta-data like all other LoRAs


—• LORA 1-6
 
 — *true* = On; *false* = Off
 — <strength> dials in the model and clip strength of the LoRA

   → when using NF4 models, all LoRAs are skipped automatically, so no errors will show up, so you can leave them on without consequence.



♦ LoRA Signal (group node)

 — <Color ON / OFF>
   → color selection to customize LoRA highlighting

 — <node_id>
   → links the color selection to the Uni Loader — AIO node
   → if the LoRA highlights seem unresponsive, check to make sure the node IDs match (Settings → Comfy → Node ID badge mode)

nodes.title: Flux versions and LoRA / ControlNet
widgets_values:
Using LoRA / ControlNet with :

 — [Checkpoint Load — AIO]       → both work perfectly fine

 — [Checkpoint Load — BNB NF4]   → LoRA: ERROR | CNet: not supported

 — [Checkpoint Load — GGUF]      → both work perfectly fine

 — [Checkpoint Load — NF4 UNET]  → LoRA: ERROR | CNet: not supported

 — [Checkpoint Load — Diffusers] → both work perfectly fine

nodes.title: IMPORTANT
widgets_values:
Make sure to pick a model for every dropdown menu slot with a selection, especially ones with an "-EXAMPLE-..." model, to avoid getting errors like this :

AttributeError: 'NoneType' object has no attribute 'lower'

which usually indicates a selection from a dropdown menu not being found on your system

nodes.title: Note — Hello!
widgets_values:
—Hello and thanks for downloading this workflow!—

► Built to provide an advanced and versatile workflow for Flux with focus on efficiency and information.


Features :

   • Compatible with all common versions of Flux
   • Full meta-data support; recognized by CivitAI 
   • Hyper-LoRA acceleration
   • LoRA support
   • ControlNet presets for Canny, Depth and HED
   • IPAdapter
   • Installation and download guide for models and nodes
   • multiple passes with optional upscales
       → 1st Pass : Noise Injection Alteration (NInjA)
       → 2nd Pass : Upscale with Upscale Model
       → 3rd Pass : Tiled Diffusion — or — UltimateSDUpscale
       → ADetailer (optional after 1st, 2nd or 3rd Pass)
       → Inpainting (optional final pass)

nodes.title: Note ←
widgets_values:
• Input Image :
  → paste the image to be inpainted here

• Mask :
  → paste the same image here and mask the inpaint area via <MaskEditor>


► MaskEditor :
The right-click context menus of these "Load Image" nodes contain the option <open in MaskEditor>, which allows marking an area manually.

   Controls:
   - mousewheel — brush size
   - ctrl + mousewheel — zoom
   - ctrl + left-click-drag — pan image


! Important : 
Even when saving the workflow with a pasted clipspace, it might be gone the next time ComfyUI is started, as clipspace images are only stored temporarily, so make sure to save images you want to keep with a save image node.

nodes.title: Note ←
widgets_values:
► Clipspace :

On any "Preview Image" node with a (Clipspace) label :
 Right-click → <Copy (Clipspace)> to copy the image's clipspace

Then it can be pasted on the "Input Image" node with :
 Right-click → <Paste (Clipspace)> to paste the image's clipspace


! Important :
Do not copy the clipspace from the before/after compare nodes

nodes.title: Note ↑
widgets_values:
• Here you can select which pass outputs you want to save
→ "Final Pass" saves the last completed pass

• Inpaint is remote controlled and needs to be enabled here and receive a "save_inpaint" signal from the [Inpainting] group to actually save.
→ without that signal it will just terminate the cue without saving 

• By default all save nodes are set up for lossless webp files with the <filename> *nth_pass_%Hours%Minutes%Seconds* 

save location → "ComfyUI\output\Flux"


• Central Control
  → just an additional all-in-one control for convenience

nodes.title: Note ↑
widgets_values:
— "VRAM Debug"
   → Frees VRAM to help prevent oom; triggered by last image pass run
   → Additional settings like <unload_all_models> might be worth trying in case of memory issues.

 — "dummy_output" 
   → ensures "VRAM Debug" is triggered at the ending

nodes.title: Note ↓
widgets_values:
► CONDITIONING

♦ Positive (group node)

  → conditioning has wildcard functionality with following formats :
   — {option a| option b|...}
   — <option a| option b|...>
   — __wildcard__ as well as __someFolder\wildcardInFolder__

The selection is based on the seed at the bottom


Using the was-node-suite here, the wildcard folder is by default :
 — "ComfyUI\custom_nodes\was-node-suite-comfyui\wildcards"

The location can be set to a different one by editing the variable "wildcards_path" found within "was_suite_config.json", located in "ComfyUI\custom_nodes\was-node-suite-comfyui"
